Makefile: translate EXTRA_CFLAGS to ccflags-y for modern kbuild

Linux 6.18's kbuild (scripts/Makefile.build) has no compatibility shim for
the legacy EXTRA_CFLAGS mechanism at all -- only ccflags-y is honored. This
Makefile routes every -I include path and every -D define it needs (all of
CONFIG_IOCTL_CFG80211, the endianness define, the include-path list for
drv_types.h/hal_data.h/etc., -O1, warning suppressions...) through
EXTRA_CFLAGS and never translates it, so under our kernel the whole set is
silently discarded. The build then fails immediately:

    core/rtw_security.c:17:10: fatal error: drv_types.h: No such file or directory

The fix is the same one-line shim upstream's own sibling driver already
carries (kelebek333/rtl8188fu's Makefile, `ccflags-y += $(EXTRA_CFLAGS)`,
inside its own `ifneq ($(KERNELRELEASE),)` block) -- this repo just never
picked it up. P3.1, PLAN.md §4.1 class E.

Not sent upstream (no CI/maintainer contact established for this pin), but
trivially reproducible: aircrack-ng/rtl8188eus PR #319 independently
attempts a broader Linux 6.19 compatibility pass covering the same root
cause among others.

diff --git a/Makefile b/Makefile
--- a/Makefile
+++ b/Makefile
@@ -1982,6 +1982,15 @@

 ifneq ($(KERNELRELEASE),)

+# Modern kbuild (this is built against Linux 6.18) does not honor the
+# legacy EXTRA_CFLAGS mechanism at all -- only ccflags-y. Every -I path and
+# -D define this Makefile sets above (all of it goes through EXTRA_CFLAGS)
+# was silently discarded without this line, which breaks the build
+# ("fatal error: drv_types.h: No such file or directory" and friends).
+# Mirrors the equivalent shim already present upstream in the sibling
+# kelebek333/rtl8188fu driver's Makefile.
+ccflags-y += $(EXTRA_CFLAGS)
+
 ########### this part for *.mk ############################
 include $(src)/hal/phydm/phydm.mk
